ipline’s historiography and to an examination of the role of intellectual frameworks and epistemic virtues in the writing of history.  afunded by Stein  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSCIENCE / History.2bisacsh2 aSteinefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030018663540uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018943840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300189438423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300189438/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY